{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/simple-abstractive-text-summarization-with-pretrained-t5-text-to-text-transfer-transformer-10f6d602c426", "time": 1683005914.848921, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/simple-abstractive-text-summarization-with-pretrained-t5-text-to-text-transfer-transformer-10f6d602c426/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Simple abstractive text summarization with pretrained T5 \u2014 Text-To-Text Transfer Transformer | by Ramsri Goutham | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Simple abstractive text summarization with pretrained T5 \u2014 Text-To-Text Transfer Transformer", "description": "T5 is a new transformer model from Google that is trained in an end-to-end manner with text as input and modified text as output. You can read more about it here. It achieves state-of-the-art results\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://ai.googleblog.com/2020/02/exploring-transfer-learning-with-t5.html", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.10683", "anchor_text": "paper", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/ramsri_goutham", "anchor_text": "Twitter.", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://www.udemy.com/course/question-generation-using-natural-language-processing/?referralCode=C8EA86A28F5398CBF763", "anchor_text": "Question generation using NLP", "paragraph_index": 10}, {"url": "https://www.learnnlp.academy/", "anchor_text": "https://www.learnnlp.academy/", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://questgen.ai/", "anchor_text": "https://questgen.ai/", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://supermeme.ai/", "anchor_text": "https://supermeme.ai/", "paragraph_index": 12}], "all_paragraphs": ["T5 is a new transformer model from Google that is trained in an end-to-end manner with text as input and modified text as output. You can read more about it here.", "It achieves state-of-the-art results on multiple NLP tasks like summarization, question answering, machine translation etc using a text-to-text transformer trained on a large text corpus.", "Today we will see how we can use huggingface\u2019s transformers library to summarize any given text. T5 is an abstractive summarization algorithm. It means that it will rewrite sentences when necessary than just picking up sentences directly from the original text.", "Install these libraries in your jupyter notebook or conda environment before you begin :", "If you see the algorithm has intelligently summarized with mentioning April although it was never mentioned in the original story. It also replaced he with the president. Cut short and removed the extra information after the comma in the sentence \u201cover 30,826 deaths \u2026.\u201d", "The same code inline as some users have reported that the Github Gist wasn\u2019t loading :", "The summarized output as mentioned above is -", "The key point to note in the code above is that we prepend our text with \u201csummarize: \u201d before passing it to the T5 summarizer.", "If you look at the paper, all we need to do for other tasks is to prepend our text with the corresponding string eg: \u201ctranslate English to German: \u201d for translation task.", "Happy NLP exploration and if you loved the content, feel free to find me on Twitter.", "If you want to learn modern NLP using transformers, check out my course Question generation using NLP", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Teaches NLP courses at https://www.learnnlp.academy/ \u25c6 Building AI SaaS Apps: https://questgen.ai/ and https://supermeme.ai/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F10f6d602c426&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsimple-abstractive-text-summariza